basics.name: Jake Dickinson
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am currently pursuing a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science at the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii, Manoa. I plan to graduate in Spring 2026, and I have a strong interest in game development.

highlights: Gained hands-on experience in technical skills such as configuring gaming PCs.
Engaged in a wide range of team-building exercises, including strategy-based games and collaborative problem-solving activities.
Competed in various esports tournaments, showcasing skills in a competitive gaming environment, while learning about communication and teamwork.
Competed in USTA events, demonstrating commitment through consistent training and match participation.
Developed skills in strategy, endurance, and sportsmanship, while working closely with coaches to improve technical aspects of the game.
Played both singles and doubles, contributing to team success with a competitive spirit through participation in several tournaments.
